President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Carol J. Galante is nominated for Assistant Secretary and Federal Housing Commissioner at the Department of Housing and Urban Development. She has experience in building mixed-income housing and managing revitalization projects. David J. Chard is nominated for a member of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences. He is currently a dean and professor at Southern Methodist University and has experience in education and research. Larry V. Hedges is also nominated for a member of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences. He is a professor of statistics at Northwestern University and has expertise in educational policy and large scale assessment. Hirokazu Yoshikawa is nominated for a member of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences. He is a professor at Harvard Graduate School of Education and focuses his research on the development of young children in diverse families and the effects of public policies on children.